        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 12 at 1:23AM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 123 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of West Glacier, or 29 miles northeast of Evergreen,
moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Many Glacier, Babb, Saint Mary, Goat Haunt, and Logan Pass.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
